<h1>Gregory Cain</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://gregorycain.net/now/">gregorycain.net/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Sacramento
CA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Independent musician; IT professional.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I create ambient music for people who want a peaceful space for contemplation, relaxation, meditation.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
Making music and designing sound bring me a lot of joy and satisfaction.  I can lose myself for hours in the process - it's where I "flow".  Being able to do something I love, and at the same time offer something to people that enriches their lives, and provides peace and healing is immensely gratifying.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Everything and everyone is connected.  Connection is not the myth - separation is the myth.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Be wrong as fast as you can - <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/06/magazine/be-wrong-as-fast-as-you-can.html">http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/06/magazine/be-wrong-as-fast-as-you-can.html</a>
</p>

